  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GCB Fund Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project consists of IFC establishing the Green Cornerstone Bond Fund of up to US$2bn that will invest in green bonds issued by financial institutions active in emerging markets, and IFC partnering with a Fund Manager to help develop the green bond market in emerging markets. Alongside the Fund, there will be an investment support facility which will provide assistance at the issuer and market level for green bonds, for research, development and knowledge sharing. The Fund will be managed by a Fixed Income asset manager selected via a Request for Proposal</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project will simultaneously stimulate the &quot;demand&quot; and the &quot;supply&quot; sides of the climate finance challenge in developing countries via fixed income markets solution.  On the demand side, the Project is providing institutional SRIs with potentially higher yields than what is available in developed markets.  Through the Fund, investors would also have access to IFC&apos;s unparalleled EM network, with a large global EM client base, accumulated knowledge, and long-term commitment to EM and private sector investments. On the supply side, the Project is providing support to FIs active in EM, who need to raise funding on a large scale to issue green bonds and finance their growing green finance activities.</narrative>
  </description>
